cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of learning with imbalanced data, which is a common issue in computer vision tasks such as object recognition and classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel approach that involves splitting the network into a classifier part and a feature extractor part, which is a common technique in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of different sampling strategies and auxiliary tasks, which are common techniques in natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition. Therefore, the paper could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
